title: PM to meet Emirati, Pakistani businessmen in UAE today
content:
ISLAMABAD, Jan 13 (APP): Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif during the second day of his visit to the United Arab Emirates (UAE) will spend a busy day on Friday where he will meet the Emirati and Pakistani businessmen.
The prime minister will meet a delegation of Abu Dhabi Chamber of Commerce, a press release from his media office said.
The prime minister will also meet Pakistani businessmen and Emirati investors in the United Arab Emirates.
Sheikh Nahyan bin Mubarak, Minister of Tolerance of the United Arab Emirates, will also call onÂ  the Prime Minister.
